main event: A civilian observed a star-like object moving north and fading out of sight over Collinsville, Illinois on November 24, 1963 at 0530Z.
interesting points: The object appeared to be a bright, solid object that looked like a star but was much brighter.
The object moved and then faded out of sight after about 5 minutes.
The observer was not wearing any glasses or visual aids when observing the object.
The observer estimated the object's speed and altitude, describing it as a 'ball, golf type'.
A neighbor was also walking to the observer's home and sighted the same object.
